      • compare

        public static boolean compare(java.util.List<java.lang.String> o1,
                              java.util.List<java.lang.String> o2,
                              java.util.function.BiPredicate<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> sc)
        this method compare each elements of List arguments using BiPredicate sc. method use sc to compare all String elements of o1 to the corresponding String element of o2. returns true, if all the elements of o1 is equals to the corresponding elements of o2 using BiPredicate sc.
        NOTE :- this method will not modify any Lists of strings given in arguments. although copy of Original Lists as argument is recommended.
        the Lists given in arguments should not be modify in parallel of this method call by any other threads.
        Parameters:
        o1 - List of String to be compare
        o2 - List of String to be compare
        sc - BiPredicate used to compare every elements.
        Returns:
        true if o1 and o2 is equals on several parameters, false otherwise.

      • removeNull

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> removeNull(java.util.List<java.lang.String> li)
        this method remove null String elements from the list of Strings li. this method create return new List including all none null elements of List li.
        NOTE :- this method will not modify List of strings given in arguments. although copy of Original List as argument is recommended.
        the List given in arguments should not be modify in parallel of this method call by any other threads.
        Parameters:
        li - List of String.
        Returns:
        new list of string generated by removing null strings from li.

      • trim

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> trim(java.util.List<java.lang.String> li)
        this method trims all String elements from the list of Strings li. this method remove preceding and trailing whitespace of all elements List li. this method create return new list containing String elements generated by applying trim operation on elements of List li.
        NOTE :- this method will not modify List of strings given in arguments. although copy of Original List as argument is recommended.
        the List given in arguments should not be modify in parallel of this method call by any other threads.
        Parameters:
        li - List of String.
        Returns:
        new list of string generated by removing preceding and trailing whitespace of elements of li.

      • splitFromWS

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> splitFromWS(java.util.List<java.lang.String> li)
        return List of string generated concatenation of arrays of strings generated by applying split operation on all elements of List li. this method first call removeNull to remove null strings. then this method apply split method to the string elements of the li. then create and return new List by concatenation of the Arrays of Strings.
        for example.. List li=new ArrayList("abc de","","fg hij k"); List nli=splitFromWS(li); System.out.println(nli);\\["abc","de","fg","hij","k"]
        NOTE :- this method will not modify List of strings given in arguments. although copy of Original List as argument is recommended.
        the List given in arguments should not be modify in parallel of this method call by any other threads.
        Parameters:
        li - list of string
        Returns:
        list of string
